other_tests.findings: The appendix is noted in retrocecal position, fluid filled and dilated up to 10 mm, with mild circumferential wall thickening and mucosal hyperemia. Mild reactive wall thickening is noted at the base of the cecum. Inflammatory fat stranding is centered around the appendiceal tip. Scattered prominent mesenteric and retroperitoneal lymph nodes are present, measuring up to 6 mm.
